{
  "schema_version": "1.0",
  "source_language": "SBM",
  "target_language": "Markdown",
  "description": "SimplexBook Markup to Markdown conversion mapping (Standard Markdown and GitHub Flavored Markdown)",
  "standards": {
    "standard_markdown": "CommonMark 0.30",
    "github_flavored_markdown": "GFM support",
    "extended_syntax": "Supports tables, task lists, and strikethrough"
  },
  "element_mappings": {
    "document_structure": {
      "sbm_book": {
        "markdown_syntax": "# {title}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Book title becomes main heading",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Use standard markdown heading"
        }
      },
      "sbm_chapter": {
        "markdown_syntax": "## {title}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Chapter becomes level 2 heading",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Use standard markdown heading"
        }
      },
      "sbm_section": {
        "markdown_syntax": "### {title}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Section becomes level 3 heading",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Use standard markdown heading"
        }
      },
      "sbm_paragraph": {
        "markdown_syntax": "{content}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Paragraph text as-is with proper spacing",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard paragraph formatting"
        }
      }
    },
    "text_formatting": {
      "sbm_bold": {
        "markdown_syntax": "**{text}**",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Bold text with double asterisks",
        "alternative_syntax": "__text__",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard bold formatting"
        }
      },
      "sbm_italic": {
        "markdown_syntax": "*{text}*",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Italic text with single asterisks",
        "alternative_syntax": "_text_",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard italic formatting"
        }
      },
      "sbm_underline": {
        "markdown_syntax": "<u>{text}</u>",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "HTML underline for non-semantic emphasis",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM allows raw HTML"
        }
      },
      "sbm_code": {
        "markdown_syntax": "`{code}`",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Inline code with backticks",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard inline code"
        }
      },
      "sbm_code_block": {
        "markdown_syntax": "```{language}\n{code}\n```",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Fenced code blocks with language specification",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM supports syntax highlighting"
        }
      },
      "sbm_superscript": {
        "markdown_syntax": "<sup>{text}</sup>",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "HTML sup tag for superscript",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM allows raw HTML"
        }
      },
      "sbm_subscript": {
        "markdown_syntax": "<sub>{text}</sub>",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "HTML sub tag for subscript",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM allows raw HTML"
        }
      },
      "sbm_strikethrough": {
        "markdown_syntax": "~~{text}~~",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Strikethrough with double tildes",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM extension"
        }
      },
      "sbm_highlight": {
        "markdown_syntax": "<mark>{text}</mark>",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Highlighted text",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM allows raw HTML"
        }
      }
    },
    "headings": {
      "sbm_h1": {
        "markdown_syntax": "# {title}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Level 1 heading",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown heading"
        }
      },
      "sbm_h2": {
        "markdown_syntax": "## {title}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Level 2 heading",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown heading"
        }
      },
      "sbm_h3": {
        "markdown_syntax": "### {title}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Level 3 heading",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown heading"
        }
      },
      "sbm_h4": {
        "markdown_syntax": "#### {title}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Level 4 heading",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown heading"
        }
      },
      "sbm_h5": {
        "markdown_syntax": "##### {title}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Level 5 heading",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown heading"
        }
      },
      "sbm_h6": {
        "markdown_syntax": "###### {title}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Level 6 heading",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown heading"
        }
      }
    },
    "lists": {
      "sbm_ordered_list": {
        "markdown_syntax": "1. {item1}\n2. {item2}\n3. {item3}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Numbered lists with period and space",
        "nested_syntax": "1. {item1}\n   1. {subitem1}\n   2. {subitem2}",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard ordered lists"
        }
      },
      "sbm_unordered_list": {
        "markdown_syntax": "- {item1}\n- {item2}\n- {item3}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Bulleted lists with hyphen, plus, or asterisk",
        "nested_syntax": "- {item1}\n  - {subitem1}\n  - {subitem2}",
        "alternative_syntax": ["* {item}", "+ {item}"],
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard unordered lists"
        }
      },
      "sbm_list_item": {
        "markdown_syntax": "- {content}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "List item content",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard list items"
        }
      },
      "sbm_definition_list": {
        "markdown_syntax": "{term}\n: {definition}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Definition lists with term followed by colon definition",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Not standard CommonMark, requires extension"
        }
      },
      "sbm_task_list": {
        "markdown_syntax": "- [ ] {task}\n- [x] {completed_task}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "GFM task lists with checkboxes",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GitHub Flavored Markdown only"
        }
      }
    },
    "links_and_references": {
      "sbm_link": {
        "markdown_syntax": "[{text}]({url})",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Inline link with descriptive text",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown links"
        }
      },
      "sbm_autolink": {
        "markdown_syntax": "<{url}>",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Automatic linking of URLs in angle brackets",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown autolinks"
        }
      },
      "sbm_email_link": {
        "markdown_syntax": "<{email}>",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Automatic linking of email addresses",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown email links"
        }
      },
      "sbm_reference_link": {
        "markdown_syntax": "[{text}][{ref}]\n\n[{ref}]: {url}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Reference-style links for reusability",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown reference links"
        }
      },
      "sbm_citation": {
        "markdown_syntax": "[{number}]",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Numeric citations in brackets",
        "alternative_syntax": "{text} []({url})",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown with brackets"
        }
      }
    },
    "tables": {
      "sbm_table": {
        "markdown_syntax": "| Header1 | Header2 | Header3 |\n|---------|---------|----------|\n| Cell1   | Cell2   | Cell3   |\n| Cell4   | Cell5   | Cell6   |",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Pipe-separated table with header row",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM table extension"
        }
      },
      "sbm_table_alignment": {
        "markdown_syntax": "| Left | Center | Right |\n|:-----|:------:|------:|\n| L    |   C    |     R |",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Table alignment using colons in header separator",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM table alignment"
        }
      }
    },
    "images": {
      "sbm_image": {
        "markdown_syntax": "![{alt_text}]({url})",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Image with alt text and URL",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown images"
        }
      },
      "sbm_image_with_title": {
        "markdown_syntax": "![{alt_text}]({url} \"{title}\")",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Image with alt text, URL, and title",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown with title attribute"
        }
      },
      "sbm_figure": {
        "markdown_syntax": "![{alt_text}]({url})\n\n*{caption}*",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Figure with image and italicized caption",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown with emphasis"
        }
      },
      "sbm_reference_image": {
        "markdown_syntax": "![{alt_text}][{ref}]\n\n[{ref}]: {url}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Reference-style images for reusability",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown reference images"
        }
      }
    },
    "block_elements": {
      "sbm_blockquote": {
        "markdown_syntax": "> {quote}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Blockquote with greater than symbol",
        "nested_syntax": "> {quote}\n> > {nested_quote}",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown blockquotes"
        }
      },
      "sbm_horizontal_rule": {
        "markdown_syntax": "---",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Horizontal rule with three or more hyphens",
        "alternative_syntax": ["***", "___"],
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown horizontal rules"
        }
      },
      "sbm_code_block": {
        "markdown_syntax": "```\n{code}\n```",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Fenced code block without language specification",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM supports syntax highlighting"
        }
      },
      "sbm_fenced_code_block": {
        "markdown_syntax": "```{language}\n{code}\n```",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Fenced code block with language for syntax highlighting",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM syntax highlighting"
        }
      }
    },
    "mathematical_content": {
      "sbm_inline_math": {
        "markdown_syntax": "${math_expression}$",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Inline mathematical expressions",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "Requires LaTeX support or MathJax"
        }
      },
      "sbm_display_math": {
        "markdown_syntax": "$$\n{math_expression}\n$$",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Block-level mathematical expressions",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "Requires LaTeX support or MathJax"
        }
      }
    },
    "special_formatting": {
      "sbm_line_break": {
        "markdown_syntax": "  \n",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Hard line break with two trailing spaces",
        "alternative_syntax": "<br>",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM allows raw HTML"
        }
      },
      "sbm_escaped_character": {
        "markdown_syntax": "\\{character}",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "Escape markdown special characters with backslash",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": false,
          "notes": "Standard markdown escaping"
        }
      },
      "sbm_html_comment": {
        "markdown_syntax": "<!-- {comment} -->",
        "attributes": {},
        "notes": "HTML comments (not visible in rendered output)",
        "gfm_extensions": {
          "extended": true,
          "notes": "GFM allows raw HTML comments"
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "conversion_rules": {
    "attribute_handling": {
      "title_conversion": {
        "sbm_attr": "title",
        "markdown_usage": "heading_text",
        "notes": "SBM title attributes become heading text"
      },
      "id_conversion": {
        "sbm_attr": "id",
        "markdown_usage": "auto_generated_anchors",
        "notes": "Markdown processors auto-generate anchors from headings"
      },
      "lang_conversion": {
        "sbm_attr": "lang",
        "markdown_usage": "not_directly_supported",
        "notes": "Language attributes not supported in basic Markdown"
      }
    },
    "content_transformation": {
      "special_characters": {
        "markdown_syntax_chars": ["*", "_", "`", "[]", "()", "#", "+", "-", ".", "!"],
        "escape_method": "prefix_with_backslash",
        "examples": {
          "\\*": "*",
          "\\_": "_",
          "\\`": "`"
        }
      },
      "html_entities": {
        "conversion_required": true,
        "common_entities": {
          "&": "&amp;",
          "<": "&lt;",
          ">": "&gt;",
          "\"": "&quot;",
          "'": "&#39;"
        }
      },
      "whitespace_handling": {
        "preserve_newlines": "in_pre_and_code_blocks_only",
        "collapse_multiple_spaces": "in_normal_text",
        "preserve_indentation": "in_code_blocks"
      }
    }
  },
  "feature_comparison": {
    "supported_features": {
      "basic_formatting": ["bold", "italic", "code", "links", "images", "headings"],
      "advanced_formatting": ["tables", "task_lists", "strikethrough", "highlighted_text"],
      "structural_elements": ["lists", "blockquotes", "horizontal_rules", "code_blocks"],
      "extensions": ["mathematical_notation", "emoji", "footnotes"]
    },
    "limitations": {
      "sbm_features_without_direct_markdown_equivalent": [
        "definition_lists", "mathematical_formulas", "complex_table_structures",
        "accessibility_metadata", "multi_language_support"
      ],
      "workaround_strategies": {
        "definition_lists": "Use HTML syntax or description text with formatting",
        "mathematical_formulas": "Use HTML with MathJax or LaTeX rendering",
        "accessibility_metadata": "Include in raw HTML or front matter",
        "complex_tables": "Use HTML table syntax within Markdown"
      }
    },
    "gfm_specific_features": {
      "enabled_by_default": ["tables", "task_lists", "strikethrough"],
      "optional_extensions": ["mathematical_notation", "footnotes", "definition_lists"],
      "syntax_highlighting": "Requires language specification in code blocks"
    }
  },
  "example_conversions": {
    "simple_document": {
      "sbm_code": "::book title=\"My Documentation\"\n::chapter title=\"Introduction\"\n::p This is a paragraph with *italic* and **bold** text.\n::ul\n::li First item\n::li Second item\n::/ul\n::/chapter\n::/book",
      "markdown_output": "# My Documentation\n\n## Introduction\n\nThis is a paragraph with *italic* and **bold** text.\n\n- First item\n- Second item"
    },
    "complex_content": {
      "sbm_code": "::chapter title=\"Advanced Features\"\n::h3 Code Examples\n::code_block language=\"python\"\nprint(\"Hello, World!\")\n::/code_block\n::h3 Links and Images\n::p Check out [this link](https://example.com)\n::p ![Description](image.png \"Title\")\n::h3 Table\n::table\n::tr ::th Header 1 ::th Header 2\n::tr ::td Cell 1 ::td Cell 2\n::/table\n::/chapter",
      "markdown_output": "## Advanced Features\n\n### Code Examples\n\n```python\nprint(\"Hello, World!\")\n```\n\n### Links and Images\n\nCheck out [this link](https://example.com)\n\n![Description](image.png \"Title\")\n\n### Table\n\n| Header 1 | Header 2 |\n|----------|----------|\n| Cell 1   | Cell 2   |"
    },
    "gfm_extensions": {
      "sbm_code": "::chapter title=\"GFM Features\"\n::task_list\n::task text=\"Complete first task\" completed=\"true\"\n::task text=\"Complete second task\" completed=\"false\"\n::/task_list\n::p ~~Strikethrough text~~\n::table\n::tr ::th Left-aligned ::th Center-aligned ::th Right-aligned\n::tr ::td L ::td C ::td R\n::/table\n::/chapter",
      "markdown_output": "## GFM Features\n\n- [x] Complete first task\n- [ ] Complete second task\n\n~~Strikethrough text~~\n\n| Left-aligned | Center-aligned | Right-aligned |\n|:-------------|:-------------:|-------------:|\n| L            | C             | R            |"
    }
  },
  "conversion_quality": {
    "lossless_conversion": {
      "supported_elements": ["text_formatting", "basic_lists", "links", "images", "code_blocks"],
      "notes": "Most basic formatting converts cleanly to Markdown"
    },
    "lossy_conversion": {
      "elements_with_loss": ["semantic_structure", "accessibility_metadata", "complex_styling"],
      "notes": "Some structural and semantic information is lost in Markdown conversion"
    },
    "manual_intervention_required": {
      "elements": ["definition_lists", "mathematical_formulas", "complex_tables"],
      "recommended_actions": "Use HTML syntax or alternative formatting"
    }
  },
  "version": "2.0",
  "last_updated": "2025-11-23",
  "compatibility": {
    "markdown_standards": ["CommonMark 0.30", "GitHub Flavored Markdown"],
    "processors": ["GitHub", "GitLab", "Pandoc", "Markdown-It", "CommonMark.js"],
    "extensions": ["MathJax", "KaTeX", "Table extensions", "Definition list extensions"]
  }
}